com.camerontec.catalys.server.test

Class EmbeddedAdapterInboundLatencyBenchmark

  • java.lang.Object
    • com.camerontec.catalys.server.test.EmbeddedAdapterInboundLatencyBenchmark
  • All Implemented Interfaces:
    IFIXListenerCallback, IFIXListenerProviderCallback, IStatefulFIXListenerCallback

    public final class EmbeddedAdapterInboundLatencyBenchmark
extends Object
implements IStatefulFIXListenerCallback, IFIXListenerProviderCallback
    Simple EmbeddedCatalysNodeAdapter based application which measures raw inbound FIX message latency across the FIX engine itself with no application level processing in place.

    Inbound messages are timestamped as soon as they are recognised as FIX messages (T1) and then another timestamp is taken on receipt of the message by the application (T2). Each latency sample is thus (T2 - T1) nanoseconds.

    On receipt of every 2^20 messages the sample histogram is displayed on the stderr stream and the internal histogram is reset.

      • storesMessages

        public boolean storesMessages()
        Description copied from interface: IStatefulFIXListenerCallback
        Return whether the specified listener expects to store messages or not.

        This method is invoked once at the time the listener is first installed.

        The return value is used by the framework to decide whether to send reused messages (for a given session) to the listener or not. If the listener expects a new message object instance each time it should return true, otherwise the framework attempts to send the same message object instance each time.

        Specified by:
        storesMessages in interface IStatefulFIXListenerCallback
        Returns:
        True if the listener expects/requires a new object instance each time, false otherwise.
